      <description>Al From was executive director of the House Democratic Caucus from 1981
            to 1985, chaired by Representative Gillis Long (D-LA). He later was the primary founder
            of the Democratic Leadership Council. Gillis Long (1923-1985) was representative for the
            8th U.S. Congressional District of Louisiana in 1963-1965 and 1973-1985. He ran
            unsuccessfully for governor of Louisiana in 1964 and 1971.</description>
